bilingual.source: My dad is at the supermarket now.
I was walking home from the supermarket.
You can buy food at the supermarket.
Li Ming and Jack are at the supermarket.

list.abstract: 《Supermarket》是由Leddra Chapman演唱的英语流行歌曲，由ALC Music Ltd发行于2013年2月18日，收录于专辑《The Crowds and Cocktails》中。

yingyinNormal.en: Mummy Rabbit has arrived at the supermarket.
yingyinNormal.zh: 兔妈妈到达了超市。

yingyinNormal.en: Supermarket. Bye. Music shop. Bye.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，超市到了！再见！乐器商店到了！再见！

yingyinNormal.en: Now imagine you live at the supermarket. Okay. No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 想像你住在超市里。好啊。不。

yingyinNormal.en: Can we go to the north pole? How about the supermarket? Yes, I don't think Teddy Playgroup has ever been shopping before.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以我们可以去趟北极吗？呃，去趟超市怎么样？可以呀，我觉得小熊泰迪它以前肯定没有去过超市。

yingyinNormal.en: Remember how horrible it was when you guys bumped into each other at the supermarket? Oh God, yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 记得你们在超市巧遇的尴尬吗？没错。

yingyinNormal.en: These are frozen soya beans, also called edamame, from the supermarket, the raw ingredient of tofu.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些都是在超市买的，速冻青豆，也叫毛豆，是做豆腐的原料。

yingyinNormal.en: Every time we go to the supermarket, though we might not know it, we're surrounded by corn.
yingyinNormal.zh: 每次我们走进超市的时候，或许我们意识不到，但我们被玉米包围了。

yingyinNormal.en: It is morning. Peppa is taking Teddy Playgroup to the supermarket. This shop sells everything.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在是早上，佩奇带着小熊泰迪来到了超市。这个商店什么都有的。

yingyinNormal.en: What you seen in jungle, this is their supermarket, and whatever they can find, that's what they kill.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那一片丛林，就是他们的超市，他们能找到什么，就杀掉什么。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《大卫·贝克汉姆：探索未知之境》

yingyinNormal.en: Can you remember, George? Dine-Saw! Dinosaur? George, there aren't any dinosaurs in the supermarket!
yingyinNormal.zh: 你能想起来吗，乔治？恐龙！恐龙？乔治，超市里根本没有恐龙！

yingyinNormal.en: OK, Rebecca, look after your auntie. Yes, Mummy. Mummy Rabbit has arrived at the supermarket.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好的，瑞贝卡，照顾好你的阿姨。好的，妈妈。兔妈妈首先来到了超市。

yingyinNormal.en: OK, Rebecca, look after your auntie. Yes, Mummy. Mummy Rabbit has arrived at the supermarket.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好的，瑞贝卡，照顾好你的阿姨。好的，妈妈。兔妈妈首先来到了超市。

yingyinNormal.en: Water. Water. Daddy Pig has reached the supermarket. All the running has made him very thirsty.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要水，我要水。猪爸爸终于到达了超市。一路跑过来让他感到非常的口渴。

yingyinNormal.en: Then luckily, my Daddy lost him at the supermarket. But we found him again in the shopping.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不过幸运的是，我的爸爸在超市把它给弄丢了。但是我们又找到了它，就在购物袋里。

yingyinNormal.en: Then luckily, my Daddy lost him at the supermarket. But we found him again in the shopping.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不过幸运的是，我的爸爸在超市把它给弄丢了。但是我们又找到了它，就在购物袋里。

yingyinNormal.en: Here people they survive. They live to live, they don't live to get rich because here there is no supermarket.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里的人为生存而活，他们自给自足，不求荣华富贵，这里你找不到超市。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《大卫·贝克汉姆：探索未知之境》

yingyinNormal.en: Driving a bus is quite hard. Selling ice-cream is quite hard. Running a supermarket check-out is quite hard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 开公共汽车确实很难。卖冰淇淋确实很难。负责一个超市的收银台确实很难。

yingyinNormal.en: Driving a bus is quite hard. Selling ice-cream is quite hard. Running a supermarket check-Out is quite hard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 开公交车还是挺难的。卖冰淇淋也挺难的。在超市的收银台为大家结账也很难。

yingyinNormal.en: Driving a bus is quite hard. Selling ice-cream is quite hard. Running a supermarket check-out is quite hard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 开公交车还是挺难的。卖冰淇淋也挺难的。在超市的收银台为大家结账也很难。

yingyinNormal.en: George, there aren't any dinosaurs in the supermarket. No, George. The next thing on the Iist is onions.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我说乔治，超市里可没有什么恐龙你知道吗？不 乔治，清单上的下一种，是洋葱。

数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。
